<h1><a name="begin_content"></a>OIG Fugitive: Etienne Allonce</h1>

<p class="charge">Allegedly submitted false claims and stole HIPAA-protected patient information.</p>


<p>Etienne Allonce was co-owner with his wife Helene Michel of Long Island, NY-based Medical Solutions Management (MSM), a company that provided medical equipment and supplies to nursing homes.</p>
<p>OIG has accused Allonce and Michel of submitting false claims to Medicare and Medicaid, including claims for supplies that were never provided.  The defendants are also charged with stealing medical records from several nursing homes to get patient private information (protected under The Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996) and then using the information to billing Medicare and Medicaid for fraudulent claims.  
Allonce is currently a fugitive, but Michel is in custody awaiting trial for her part in these activities. </p>

